  "description": [
    "JENNY LIND COMBEST SECOND FROM LEFT OF MOSS POINT MAPS WITH OTHERS plans for a research project in iwing computers to design school bus routes at Ole Miss Working in the project from left are Otis Williams Lepanto Ark Miss Combest Mrs Wil liams Dr Roscoe A Boyer director of the project George Clement of Amory UM photo Research grants mean funds to many students Ole Miss hires Moss Point girl as student helper UNIVERSITY what does it mean when a university receives a research grant from a federal agency or from private indus try According to Dr Roscoe A Boyer of the school of education at the University of Mississippi In addition to the value of the re search performed it means money in the pockets of many tudents In frequent cases for some students it means the difference beitween continuing a college ed ucation or being forced to drop out for financial reasons A research grant can pay either part or all of a students college expenses and can also be of great benefit to the uni versity In 1961 the US office of educa tion issued a grant of 38000 to Ole Miss for the purpose of"
